cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DB. 

The paper deals with natural language processing and information retrieval techniques to extract interesting trivia from Wikipedia pages of entities. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses machine learning techniques to rank the trivia based on their interestingness, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of features to rank the trivia also falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and the extraction of information from Wikipedia pages falls under cs.DB (Databases).
